Fleet Planner

As a fleet planner at Van den Bosch Iberia in Barcelona (Spain), your responsibilities lie in the daily management of our drivers. You will be part of Team Trucking at our Barcelona office and with your fellow fleet planners and truck planners. Together with the other planners, you will be responsible for the operational coordination of international transports within Spain, Portugal and southern France.

We are Van den Bosch – The Supply Changer in Bulk. We believe bulk logistics can be approached smarter. Our mission is to create sustainable and tangible change in the sector through innovation, passion, expertise, and ambition.

As part of that mission, you will play a key role in making our smart bulk logistics a reality. You are responsible for your own group of drivers and trucks. You ensure that both productivity and quality of work are continuously improved. In close cooperation with the Truck Planners you translate the schedules to the drivers so that the trips are executed as efficiently as possible. You will also work with the customer service and master planning team to ensure a smooth operational flow. A proactive attitude and clear communication are therefore indispensable. You make our fleets run as efficiently as possible!

Knowledge of bulk transport is nice to have, but this is not a requirement. To get to know Van den Bosch and our industry, you will participate in the extensive induction programme at our headquarters in the Netherlands. After this is completed, you will join your colleagues to start working on your own. In this position, it is important that you are strong and can switch quickly to keep the operation running.

Your Profile
You have at least 3 years of experience as a planner, affinity with transport is a must;
Experience in working with drivers and managing their schedules;
Good command of English and Spanish, French and/or Portuguese is an advantage;
Excellent communication skills;
Currently living in or near Barcelona.
Our offer
Work at an organization that was again selected as a World-class Workplace in 2024;
A comprehensive onboarding program to familiarize yourself with Van den Bosch and give you a flying start;
Ample opportunity for personal development and study options;
A challenging role within an ambitious and forward-thinking organization.

We are looking forward to your application!

